---
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service — Lantern" description="Lantern's terms of service. Read the terms that govern your use of Lantern.">
	<Header />
	<main class="legal">
		<div class="legal-inner">
			<h1>Terms of Service</h1>
			<p class="effective">Effective date: April 8, 2026</p>

			<p>
				These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your access to and use of Lantern ("the Service"), operated by Lantern ("we", "us", "our"). By creating an account or using the Service, you agree to these Terms.
			</p>

			<h2>1. Eligibility</h2>
			<p>
				You must be at least 16 years old and have the authority to bind your organization to these Terms. By using the Service, you represent that you meet these requirements.
			</p>

			<h2>2. Account</h2>
			<p>
				You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials and for all activities that occur under your account. You must notify us immediately of any unauthorized use of your account.
			</p>

			<h2>3. Acceptable Use</h2>
			<p>You agree not to:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Use the Service for any unlawful purpose</li>
				<li>Attempt to reverse-engineer, decompile, or extract the source code of the Service</li>
				<li>Resell, redistribute, or sublicense access to the Service or its data without our prior written consent</li>
				<li>Use the Service to harass, defame, or harm any individual or organization</li>
				<li>Interfere with or disrupt the integrity or performance of the Service</li>
				<li>Circumvent any usage limits, rate limits, or access restrictions</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>4. Subscriptions and Payments</h2>
			<p>
				Lantern offers Free, Starter, Pro, and Team plans. Paid plans are billed monthly or annually as selected at the time of purchase. All fees are non-refundable except where required by applicable law.
			</p>
			<p>
				We may change pricing at any time. Price changes to existing subscriptions will take effect at the start of the next billing cycle, and we will provide at least 30 days' notice before applying the change.
			</p>

			<h2>5. Free Plan</h2>
			<p>
				The Free plan is provided at our discretion and may be modified or discontinued at any time. Free plan data is retained for 7 days as described in our plan features.
			</p>

			<h2>6. Cancellation</h2>
			<p>
				You may cancel your subscription at any time through your account settings. Upon cancellation, you retain access to paid features until the end of your current billing period. After that, your account will revert to the Free plan. Annual subscriptions are non-refundable for the remainder of the billing period after cancellation.
			</p>

			<h2>7. Data and Content</h2>
			<p>
				Competitive intelligence data provided by Lantern is compiled from publicly available sources. We do not guarantee the accuracy, completeness, or timeliness of this data. You are responsible for how you use the insights and battle cards generated by the Service.
			</p>
			<p>
				You retain ownership of any data you upload or configure in the Service (e.g., competitor selections, webhook URLs). We retain a license to process this data solely to provide the Service to you.
			</p>

			<h2>8. AI-Generated Content</h2>
			<p>
				Lantern uses artificial intelligence to generate insights, change summaries, and battle cards. AI-generated content may contain inaccuracies. You should verify AI-generated content before relying on it for business decisions. We are not liable for actions taken based on AI-generated content.
			</p>

			<h2>9. Intellectual Property</h2>
			<p>
				The Service, including its design, features, code, and documentation, is owned by Lantern and protected by intellectual property laws. These Terms do not grant you any rights to our trademarks, logos, or branding.
			</p>

			<h2>10. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
			<p>
				The Service is provided "as is" and "as available" without warranties of any kind, whether express or implied, including but not limited to implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement.
			</p>

			<h2>11. Limitation of Liability</h2>
			<p>
				To the maximum extent permitted by law, Lantern shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or any loss of profits or revenues, whether incurred directly or indirectly, arising from your use of or inability to use the Service.
			</p>
			<p>
				Our total aggregate liability for any claims arising out of or relating to the Service shall not exceed the amount you paid to us in the 12 months preceding the claim.
			</p>

			<h2>12. Indemnification</h2>
			<p>
				You agree to indemnify and hold harmless Lantern from any claims, damages, or expenses arising from your use of the Service or violation of these Terms.
			</p>

			<h2>13. Modifications to the Service</h2>
			<p>
				We reserve the right to modify, suspend, or discontinue the Service (or any part thereof) at any time, with or without notice. We will make reasonable efforts to notify you of material changes.
			</p>

			<h2>14. Changes to These Terms</h2>
			<p>
				We may revise these Terms from time to time. We will notify you of material changes by posting the updated Terms on this page and updating the effective date. Your continued use of the Service after changes constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.
			</p>

			<h2>15. Governing Law</h2>
			<p>
				These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with applicable law, without regard to conflict of law principles.
			</p>

			<h2>16. Contact Us</h2>
			<p>
				If you have questions about these Terms, please contact us at
				<a href="mailto:hi@lanternci.com">hi@lanternci.com</a>.
			</p>
		</div>
	</main>
	<Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
	.legal {
		padding: 64px 24px 80px;
	}
	.legal-inner {
		max-width: 720px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}
	.legal-inner h1 {
		font-size: 32px;
		font-weight: 700;
		margin-bottom: 8px;
	}
	.effective {
		font-size: 14px;
		color: var(--text-tertiary);
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}
	.legal-inner h2 {
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 600;
		margin-top: 40px;
		margin-bottom: 12px;
	}
	.legal-inner p {
		font-size: 15px;
		color: var(--text-secondary);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin-bottom: 12px;
	}
	.legal-inner ul {
		padding-left: 20px;
		margin-bottom: 12px;
	}
	.legal-inner li {
		font-size: 15px;
		color: var(--text-secondary);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin-bottom: 4px;
	}
	.legal-inner a {
		color: var(--brand-primary);
	}
	.legal-inner a:hover {
		text-decoration: underline;
	}
</style>
